# Lint generated files (after generation complete)

**When:** You have **finished** generating or editing code. Do **not** run lint during or in the middle of generation or thinking—only after the full response or edit is complete.

## Rule

1. **After** you complete a code generation or edit, run the appropriate linter on the **files you created or modified**.
2. **Do not** run lint while the user is still receiving streamed output or while you are still applying edits.
3. Prefer **scoped lint** on changed paths so feedback is fast and relevant.

## Commands by file type

| Files changed | Lint command (from repo root) |
|---------------|-------------------------------|
| Python (`python/**/*.py`) | `uv run ruff check <paths>` then `uv run ruff format --check <paths>` (or `ruff format <paths>` to fix) |
| C++ (`native/**/*.cpp`, `native/**/*.h`) | `just lint` (full) or run cppcheck/clang-tidy on listed files if script supports it |
| Shell (`scripts/*.sh`) | `shellcheck <paths>` or `just lint-shell` |
| Ansible (`ansible/**/*.yml`) | `ansible-lint` on changed playbooks/roles |
| TypeScript/JS (`web/**`, `tui-e2e/**`) | `just lint` (includes ESLint) or run from `web/` / `tui-e2e/` |

**Example (Python only):**
```bash
# After editing python/tui/app.py and python/integration/combo_detector.py
uv run ruff check python/tui/app.py python/integration/combo_detector.py
uv run ruff format python/tui/app.py python/integration/combo_detector.py
```

**Full project lint (when many files or unclear scope):**
- `just lint` or `lint:run` — runs all linters (slower).
- `just lint-parallel` — same, in parallel.

## Hook (pre-commit)

A pre-commit hook runs **only on staged files** at commit time, so “generation complete” is when the user stages and commits. See `scripts/lint_staged.sh` and `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (local hook `lint-staged`). Install with `pre-commit install`.
